Merge pull request #143 from daipom/add-open-auto-path

SocketManager: Enable `open(nil)` to select path automatically

commit.message:
SocketManager: Enable open(nil) selecting path automatically

This `open(nil)` selects `path` automatically.

Especially on Windows, it is hard to search a available port for `path`,
so we should use this feature.
(The current `generate_path` logic sometimes chooses unavailable port.
For example, it does not consider the excluded port range.)

Note: This fix keeps backward compatibility.

Signed-off-by: Daijiro Fukuda <fukuda@clear-code.com>

Consider excluded port ranges for Windows

Some applications such as Hyper-V or Docker use excluded port range so
that other applications can't use those ports.
We need to exclude those ports for choosing port number.

Signed-off-by: Daijiro Fukuda <fukuda@clear-code.com>

Treat worker unexpected shutdown as Warn log level

This log level was changed to ERROR by the fix: 4d6dbd3d1b4e1af88cc2593b5b19cf0f6da7d5dd.
However, this log is outputted when using SIGHUP, so ERROR is too strong.
Leave it as Warn as an adjustment for now.

Before

  2022-11-29 18:47:47 +0900 [error]: fluent/log.rb:372:error: Worker 0 finished unexpectedly with status 0

After

  2022-11-29 18:45:42 +0900 [warn]: fluent/log.rb:351:warn: Worker 0 finished unexpectedly with status 0

Merge pull request #127 from treasure-data/reopen-log

Reopen log file when rotation is detected

commit.message:
Reopen log file when rotation is detected

In the previous vesions, there was no way to detect log rotation event when
log file was rotated by external tool (logrotate)

It causes that DaemonLogger continues to write logs to rotated file even even
when it's already renamed or removed, it's not expected behavior.

This commit fixes by reopening log file when inode is changed.

Signed-off-by: Takuro Ashie <ashie@clear-code.com>

commit.message:
Fix behavior of start_worker_delay

Example: start_worker_delay 3

before

0s: start worker-0
3s: start worker-1
3s: start worker-2
6s: start worker-3
6s: start worker-4

after

0s: start worker-0
3s: start worker-1
6s: start worker-2
9s: start worker-3
12s: start worker-4
